snippet: Tina Maze of Slovenia won the super-G in St. Anton, Austria, on Sunday and became the sixth woman to win a World Cup race in all five Alpine disciplines.
abstract: Skier Tina Maze of Slovenia wins World Cup super-G in St Anton, Austria.
lead_paragraph: Tina Maze of Slovenia won the super-G in St. Anton, Austria, on Sunday and became the sixth woman to win a World Cup race in all five Alpine disciplines.

headline.main: Maze Wins Super-G World Cup Race
